var book = {
	"name": "Nehemiah",
	"numChapters": 13,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>The words of Nehemiah son of Hakaliah:In the month of Kislev<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12298A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12298A\"></sup> in the twentieth year, while I was in the citadel of Susa,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12298B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12298B\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Hanani,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12299C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12299C\"></sup> one of my brothers, came from Judah with some other men, and I questioned them about the Jewish remnant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12299D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12299D\"></sup> that had survived the exile, and also about Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They said to me, “Those who survived the exile and are back in the province are in great trouble and disgrace. The wall of Jerusalem is broken down, and its gates have been burned with fire.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12300E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12300E\"></sup>”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When I heard these things, I sat down and wept.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12301F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12301F\"></sup> For some days I mourned and fasted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12301G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12301G\"></sup> and prayed before the God of heaven.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then I said:“<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of heaven, the great and awesome God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12302H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12302H\"></sup> who keeps his covenant of love<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12302I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12302I\"></sup> with those who love him and keep his commandments,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>let your ear be attentive and your eyes open to hear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12303J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12303J\"></sup> the prayer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12303K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12303K\"></sup> your servant is praying before you day and night for your servants, the people of Israel. I confess<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12303L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12303L\"></sup> the sins we Israelites, including myself and my father’s family, have committed against you.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>We have acted very wickedly<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12304M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12304M\"></sup> toward you. We have not obeyed the commands, decrees and laws you gave your servant Moses.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“Remember<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12305N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12305N\"></sup> the instruction you gave your servant Moses, saying, ‘If you are unfaithful, I will scatter<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12305O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12305O\"></sup> you among the nations,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>but if you return to me and obey my commands, then even if your exiled people are at the farthest horizon, I will gather<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12306P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12306P\"></sup> them from there and bring them to the place I have chosen as a dwelling for my Name.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12306Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12306Q\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“They are your servants and your people, whom you redeemed by your great strength and your mighty hand.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12307R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12307R\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Lord, let your ear be attentive<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12308S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12308S\"></sup> to the prayer of this your servant and to the prayer of your servants who delight in revering your name. Give your servant success today by granting him favor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12308T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12308T\"></sup> in the presence of this man.”I was cupbearer<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12308U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12308U\"></sup> to the king."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>In the month of Nisan in the twentieth year of King Artaxerxes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12309A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12309A\"></sup> when wine was brought for him, I took the wine and gave it to the king. I had not been sad in his presence before,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>so the king asked me, “Why does your face look so sad when you are not ill? This can be nothing but sadness of heart.”I was very much afraid,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>but I said to the king, “May the king live forever!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12311B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12311B\"></sup> Why should my face not look sad when the city<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12311C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12311C\"></sup> where my ancestors are buried lies in ruins, and its gates have been destroyed by fire?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12311D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12311D\"></sup>”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The king said to me, “What is it you want?”Then I prayed to the God of heaven,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and I answered the king, “If it pleases the king and if your servant has found favor in his sight, let him send me to the city in Judah where my ancestors are buried so that I can rebuild it.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then the king<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12314E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12314E\"></sup>, with the queen sitting beside him, asked me, “How long will your journey take, and when will you get back?” It pleased the king to send me; so I set a time.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I also said to him, “If it pleases the king, may I have letters to the governors of Trans-Euphrates,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12315F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12315F\"></sup> so that they will provide me safe-conduct until I arrive in Judah?",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And may I have a letter to Asaph, keeper of the royal park, so he will give me timber to make beams for the gates of the citadel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12316G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12316G\"></sup> by the temple and for the city wall and for the residence I will occupy?” And because the gracious hand of my God was on me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12316H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12316H\"></sup> the king granted my requests.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12316I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12316I\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So I went to the governors of Trans-Euphrates and gave them the king’s letters. The king had also sent army officers and cavalry<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12317J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12317J\"></sup> with me.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When Sanballat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12318K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12318K\"></sup> the Horonite and Tobiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12318L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12318L\"></sup> the Ammonite official heard about this, they were very much disturbed that someone had come to promote the welfare of the Israelites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12318M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12318M\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>I went to Jerusalem, and after staying there three days<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12319N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12319N\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>I set out during the night with a few others. I had not told anyone what my God had put in my heart to do for Jerusalem. There were no mounts with me except the one I was riding on.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>By night I went out through the Valley Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12321O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12321O\"></sup> toward the Jackal Well and the Dung Gate,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12321P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12321P\"></sup> examining the walls<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12321Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12321Q\"></sup> of Jerusalem, which had been broken down, and its gates, which had been destroyed by fire.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then I moved on toward the Fountain Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12322R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12322R\"></sup> and the King’s Pool,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12322S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12322S\"></sup> but there was not enough room for my mount to get through;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>so I went up the valley by night, examining the wall. Finally, I turned back and reentered through the Valley Gate.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The officials did not know where I had gone or what I was doing, because as yet I had said nothing to the Jews or the priests or nobles or officials or any others who would be doing the work.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then I said to them, “You see the trouble we are in: Jerusalem lies in ruins, and its gates have been burned with fire.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12325T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12325T\"></sup> Come, let us rebuild the wall<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12325U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12325U\"></sup> of Jerusalem, and we will no longer be in disgrace.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12325V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12325V\"></sup>”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>I also told them about the gracious hand of my God on me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12326W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12326W\"></sup> and what the king had said to me.They replied, “Let us start rebuilding.” So they began this good work.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But when Sanballat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12327X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12327X\"></sup> the Horonite, Tobiah the Ammonite official and Geshem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12327Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12327Y\"></sup> the Arab heard about it, they mocked and ridiculed us.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12327Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12327Z\"></sup> “What is this you are doing?” they asked. “Are you rebelling against the king?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>I answered them by saying, “The God of heaven will give us success. We his servants will start rebuilding,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12328AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12328AA\"></sup> but as for you, you have no share<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12328AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12328AB\"></sup> in Jerusalem or any claim or historic right to it.”"
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>Eliashib<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12329A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12329A\"></sup> the high priest and his fellow priests went to work and rebuilt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12329B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12329B\"></sup> the Sheep Gate.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12329C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12329C\"></sup> They dedicated it and set its doors in place, building as far as the Tower of the Hundred, which they dedicated, and as far as the Tower of Hananel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12329D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12329D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The men of Jericho<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12330E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12330E\"></sup> built the adjoining section, and Zakkur son of Imri built next to them.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The Fish Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12331F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12331F\"></sup> was rebuilt by the sons of Hassenaah. They laid its beams and put its doors and bolts and bars in place.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Meremoth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12332G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12332G\"></sup> son of Uriah, the son of Hakkoz, repaired the next section. Next to him Meshullam son of Berekiah, the son of Meshezabel, made repairs, and next to him Zadok son of Baana also made repairs.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The next section was repaired by the men of Tekoa,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12333H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12333H\"></sup> but their nobles would not put their shoulders to the work under their supervisors.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The Jeshanah Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12334I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12334I\"></sup> was repaired by Joiada son of Paseah and Meshullam son of Besodeiah. They laid its beams and put its doors with their bolts and bars in place.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Next to them, repairs were made by men from Gibeon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12335J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12335J\"></sup> and Mizpah—Melatiah of Gibeon and Jadon of Meronoth—places under the authority of the governor of Trans-Euphrates.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Uzziel son of Harhaiah, one of the goldsmiths, repaired the next section; and Hananiah, one of the perfume-makers, made repairs next to that. They restored Jerusalem as far as the Broad Wall.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12336K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12336K\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Rephaiah son of Hur, ruler of a half-district of Jerusalem, repaired the next section.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Adjoining this, Jedaiah son of Harumaph made repairs opposite his house, and Hattush son of Hashabneiah made repairs next to him.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Malkijah son of Harim and Hasshub son of Pahath-Moab repaired another section and the Tower of the Ovens.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12339L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12339L\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Shallum son of Hallohesh, ruler of a half-district of Jerusalem, repaired the next section with the help of his daughters.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The Valley Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12341M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12341M\"></sup> was repaired by Hanun and the residents of Zanoah.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12341N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12341N\"></sup> They rebuilt it and put its doors with their bolts and bars in place. They also repaired a thousand cubits of the wall as far as the Dung Gate.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12341O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12341O\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The Dung Gate was repaired by Malkijah son of Rekab, ruler of the district of Beth Hakkerem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12342P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12342P\"></sup> He rebuilt it and put its doors with their bolts and bars in place.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The Fountain Gate was repaired by Shallun son of Kol-Hozeh, ruler of the district of Mizpah. He rebuilt it, roofing it over and putting its doors and bolts and bars in place. He also repaired the wall of the Pool of Siloam,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12343Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12343Q\"></sup> by the King’s Garden, as far as the steps going down from the City of David.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Beyond him, Nehemiah son of Azbuk, ruler of a half-district of Beth Zur,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12344R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12344R\"></sup> made repairs up to a point opposite the tombs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12344S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12344S\"></sup> of David, as far as the artificial pool and the House of the Heroes.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Next to him, the repairs were made by the Levites under Rehum son of Bani. Beside him, Hashabiah, ruler of half the district of Keilah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12345T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12345T\"></sup> carried out repairs for his district.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Next to him, the repairs were made by their fellow Levites under Binnui son of Henadad, ruler of the other half-district of Keilah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Next to him, Ezer son of Jeshua, ruler of Mizpah, repaired another section, from a point facing the ascent to the armory as far as the angle of the wall.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Next to him, Baruch son of Zabbai zealously repaired another section, from the angle to the entrance of the house of Eliashib the high priest.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Next to him, Meremoth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12349U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12349U\"></sup> son of Uriah, the son of Hakkoz, repaired another section, from the entrance of Eliashib’s house to the end of it.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The repairs next to him were made by the priests from the surrounding region.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Beyond them, Benjamin and Hasshub made repairs in front of their house; and next to them, Azariah son of Maaseiah, the son of Ananiah, made repairs beside his house.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Next to him, Binnui<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12352V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12352V\"></sup> son of Henadad repaired another section, from Azariah’s house to the angle and the corner,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>and Palal son of Uzai worked opposite the angle and the tower projecting from the upper palace near the court of the guard.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12353W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12353W\"></sup> Next to him, Pedaiah son of Parosh<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12353X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12353X\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and the temple servants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12354Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12354Y\"></sup> living on the hill of Ophel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12354Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12354Z\"></sup> made repairs up to a point opposite the Water Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12354AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12354AA\"></sup> toward the east and the projecting tower.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Next to them, the men of Tekoa<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12355AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12355AB\"></sup> repaired another section, from the great projecting tower<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12355AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12355AC\"></sup> to the wall of Ophel.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Above the Horse Gate,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12356AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12356AD\"></sup> the priests made repairs, each in front of his own house.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Next to them, Zadok son of Immer made repairs opposite his house. Next to him, Shemaiah son of Shekaniah, the guard at the East Gate, made repairs.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Next to him, Hananiah son of Shelemiah, and Hanun, the sixth son of Zalaph, repaired another section. Next to them, Meshullam son of Berekiah made repairs opposite his living quarters.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Next to him, Malkijah, one of the goldsmiths, made repairs as far as the house of the temple servants and the merchants, opposite the Inspection Gate, and as far as the room above the corner;",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>and between the room above the corner and the Sheep Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12360AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12360AE\"></sup> the goldsmiths and merchants made repairs."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>When Sanballat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12361A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12361A\"></sup> heard that we were rebuilding the wall, he became angry and was greatly incensed. He ridiculed the Jews,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and in the presence of his associates<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12362B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12362B\"></sup> and the army of Samaria, he said, “What are those feeble Jews doing? Will they restore their wall? Will they offer sacrifices? Will they finish in a day? Can they bring the stones back to life from those heaps of rubble<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12362C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12362C\"></sup>—burned as they are?”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Tobiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12363D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12363D\"></sup> the Ammonite, who was at his side, said, “What they are building—even a fox climbing up on it would break down their wall of stones!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12363E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12363E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Hear us, our God, for we are despised.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12364F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12364F\"></sup> Turn their insults back on their own heads. Give them over as plunder in a land of captivity.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Do not cover up their guilt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12365G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12365G\"></sup> or blot out their sins from your sight,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12365H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12365H\"></sup> for they have thrown insults in the face of the builders.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So we rebuilt the wall till all of it reached half its height, for the people worked with all their heart.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But when Sanballat, Tobiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12367I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12367I\"></sup> the Arabs, the Ammonites and the people of Ashdod heard that the repairs to Jerusalem’s walls had gone ahead and that the gaps were being closed, they were very angry.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They all plotted together<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12368J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12368J\"></sup> to come and fight against Jerusalem and stir up trouble against it.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But we prayed to our God and posted a guard day and night to meet this threat.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Meanwhile, the people in Judah said, “The strength of the laborers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12370K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12370K\"></sup> is giving out, and there is so much rubble that we cannot rebuild the wall.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Also our enemies said, “Before they know it or see us, we will be right there among them and will kill them and put an end to the work.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the Jews who lived near them came and told us ten times over, “Wherever you turn, they will attack us.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Therefore I stationed some of the people behind the lowest points of the wall at the exposed places, posting them by families, with their swords, spears and bows.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>After I looked things over, I stood up and said to the nobles, the officials and the rest of the people, “Don’t be afraid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12374L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12374L\"></sup> of them. Remember<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12374M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12374M\"></sup> the Lord, who is great and awesome,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12374N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12374N\"></sup> and fight<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12374O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12374O\"></sup> for your families, your sons and your daughters, your wives and your homes.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When our enemies heard that we were aware of their plot and that God had frustrated it,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12375P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12375P\"></sup> we all returned to the wall, each to our own work.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>From that day on, half of my men did the work, while the other half were equipped with spears, shields, bows and armor. The officers posted themselves behind all the people of Judah",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>who were building the wall. Those who carried materials did their work with one hand and held a weapon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12377Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12377Q\"></sup> in the other,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and each of the builders wore his sword at his side as he worked. But the man who sounded the trumpet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12378R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12378R\"></sup> stayed with me.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then I said to the nobles, the officials and the rest of the people, “The work is extensive and spread out, and we are widely separated from each other along the wall.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Wherever you hear the sound of the trumpet,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12380S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12380S\"></sup> join us there. Our God will fight<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12380T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12380T\"></sup> for us!”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So we continued the work with half the men holding spears, from the first light of dawn till the stars came out.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>At that time I also said to the people, “Have every man and his helper stay inside Jerusalem at night, so they can serve us as guards by night and as workers by day.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Neither I nor my brothers nor my men nor the guards with me took off our clothes; each had his weapon, even when he went for water."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>Now the men and their wives raised a great outcry against their fellow Jews.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Some were saying, “We and our sons and daughters are numerous; in order for us to eat and stay alive, we must get grain.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Others were saying, “We are mortgaging our fields,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12386A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12386A\"></sup> our vineyards and our homes to get grain during the famine.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12386B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12386B\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Still others were saying, “We have had to borrow money to pay the king’s tax<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12387C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12387C\"></sup> on our fields and vineyards.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Although we are of the same flesh and blood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12388D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12388D\"></sup> as our fellow Jews and though our children are as good as theirs, yet we have to subject our sons and daughters to slavery.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12388E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12388E\"></sup> Some of our daughters have already been enslaved, but we are powerless, because our fields and our vineyards belong to others.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12388F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12388F\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When I heard their outcry and these charges, I was very angry.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I pondered them in my mind and then accused the nobles and officials. I told them, “You are charging your own people interest!”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12390G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12390G\"></sup> So I called together a large meeting to deal with them",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and said: “As far as possible, we have bought<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12391H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12391H\"></sup> back our fellow Jews who were sold to the Gentiles. Now you are selling your own people, only for them to be sold back to us!” They kept quiet, because they could find nothing to say.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12391I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12391I\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So I continued, “What you are doing is not right. Shouldn’t you walk in the fear of our God to avoid the reproach<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12392J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12392J\"></sup> of our Gentile enemies?",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>I and my brothers and my men are also lending the people money and grain. But let us stop charging interest!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12393K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12393K\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Give back to them immediately their fields, vineyards, olive groves and houses, and also the interest<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12394L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12394L\"></sup> you are charging them—one percent of the money, grain, new wine and olive oil.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“We will give it back,” they said. “And we will not demand anything more from them. We will do as you say.”Then I summoned the priests and made the nobles and officials take an oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12395M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12395M\"></sup> to do what they had promised.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I also shook<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12396N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12396N\"></sup> out the folds of my robe and said, “In this way may God shake out of their house and possessions anyone who does not keep this promise. So may such a person be shaken out and emptied!”At this the whole assembly said, “Amen,”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12396O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12396O\"></sup> and praised the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And the people did as they had promised.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Moreover, from the twentieth year of King Artaxerxes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12397P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12397P\"></sup> when I was appointed to be their governor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12397Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12397Q\"></sup> in the land of Judah, until his thirty-second year—twelve years—neither I nor my brothers ate the food allotted to the governor.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But the earlier governors—those preceding me—placed a heavy burden on the people and took forty shekels of silver from them in addition to food and wine. Their assistants also lorded it over the people. But out of reverence for God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12398R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12398R\"></sup> I did not act like that.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Instead,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12399S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12399S\"></sup> I devoted myself to the work on this wall. All my men were assembled there for the work; we did not acquire any land.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Furthermore, a hundred and fifty Jews and officials ate at my table, as well as those who came to us from the surrounding nations.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Each day one ox, six choice sheep and some poultry<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12401T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12401T\"></sup> were prepared for me, and every ten days an abundant supply of wine of all kinds. In spite of all this, I never demanded the food allotted to the governor, because the demands were heavy on these people.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Remember<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12402U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12402U\"></sup> me with favor, my God, for all I have done for these people."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>When word came to Sanballat, Tobiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12403A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12403A\"></sup> Geshem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12403B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12403B\"></sup> the Arab and the rest of our enemies that I had rebuilt the wall and not a gap was left in it—though up to that time I had not set the doors in the gates—",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Sanballat and Geshem sent me this message: “Come, let us meet together in one of the villages on the plain of Ono.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12404C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12404C\"></sup>”But they were scheming to harm me;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>so I sent messengers to them with this reply: “I am carrying on a great project and cannot go down. Why should the work stop while I leave it and go down to you?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Four times they sent me the same message, and each time I gave them the same answer.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then, the fifth time, Sanballat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12407D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12407D\"></sup> sent his aide to me with the same message, and in his hand was an unsealed letter",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>in which was written:“It is reported among the nations—and Geshem<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12408E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12408E\"></sup> says it is true—that you and the Jews are plotting to revolt, and therefore you are building the wall. Moreover, according to these reports you are about to become their king",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and have even appointed prophets to make this proclamation about you in Jerusalem: ‘There is a king in Judah!’ Now this report will get back to the king; so come, let us meet together.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I sent him this reply: “Nothing like what you are saying is happening; you are just making it up out of your head.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They were all trying to frighten us, thinking, “Their hands will get too weak for the work, and it will not be completed.”But I prayed, “Now strengthen my hands.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>One day I went to the house of Shemaiah son of Delaiah, the son of Mehetabel, who was shut in at his home. He said, “Let us meet in the house of God, inside the temple<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12412F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12412F\"></sup>, and let us close the temple doors, because men are coming to kill you—by night they are coming to kill you.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But I said, “Should a man like me run away? Or should someone like me go into the temple to save his life? I will not go!”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>I realized that God had not sent him, but that he had prophesied against me<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12414G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12414G\"></sup> because Tobiah and Sanballat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12414H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12414H\"></sup> had hired him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He had been hired to intimidate me so that I would commit a sin by doing this, and then they would give me a bad name to discredit me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12415I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12415I\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Remember<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12416J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12416J\"></sup> Tobiah and Sanballat,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12416K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12416K\"></sup> my God, because of what they have done; remember also the prophet<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12416L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12416L\"></sup> Noadiah and how she and the rest of the prophets<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12416M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12416M\"></sup> have been trying to intimidate me.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So the wall was completed on the twenty-fifth of Elul, in fifty-two days.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When all our enemies heard about this, all the surrounding nations were afraid and lost their self-confidence, because they realized that this work had been done with the help of our God.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Also, in those days the nobles of Judah were sending many letters to Tobiah, and replies from Tobiah kept coming to them.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>For many in Judah were under oath to him, since he was son-in-law to Shekaniah son of Arah, and his son Jehohanan had married the daughter of Meshullam son of Berekiah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Moreover, they kept reporting to me his good deeds and then telling him what I said. And Tobiah sent letters to intimidate me."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>After the wall had been rebuilt and I had set the doors in place, the gatekeepers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12422A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12422A\"></sup> the musicians<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12422B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12422B\"></sup> and the Levites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12422C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12422C\"></sup> were appointed.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I put in charge of Jerusalem my brother Hanani,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12423D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12423D\"></sup> along with Hananiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12423E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12423E\"></sup> the commander of the citadel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12423F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12423F\"></sup> because he was a man of integrity and feared<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12423G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12423G\"></sup> God more than most people do.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I said to them, “The gates of Jerusalem are not to be opened until the sun is hot. While the gatekeepers are still on duty, have them shut the doors and bar them. Also appoint residents of Jerusalem as guards, some at their posts and some near their own houses.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now the city was large and spacious, but there were few people in it,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12425I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12425I\"></sup> and the houses had not yet been rebuilt.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So my God put it into my heart to assemble the nobles, the officials and the common people for registration by families. I found the genealogical record of those who had been the first to return. This is what I found written there:",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>These are the people of the province who came up from the captivity of the exiles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12427J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12427J\"></sup> whom Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon had taken captive (they returned to Jerusalem and Judah, each to his own town,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>in company with Zerubbabel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12428K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12428K\"></sup> Joshua, Nehemiah, Azariah, Raamiah, Nahamani, Mordecai, Bilshan, Mispereth, Bigvai, Nehum and Baanah):The list of the men of Israel:",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>The priests:",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>The Levites:",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>The musicians:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12465T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12465T\"></sup>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>The gatekeepers:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12466U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12466U\"></sup>",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>The temple servants:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12467V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12467V\"></sup>",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>The descendants of the servants of Solomon:",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>The following came up from the towns of Tel Melah, Tel Harsha, Kerub, Addon and Immer, but they could not show that their families were descended from Israel:",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>And from among the priests:",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>These searched for their family records, but they could not find them and so were excluded from the priesthood as unclean.",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>The governor, therefore, ordered them not to eat any of the most sacred food until there should be a priest ministering with the Urim and Thummim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12486X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12486X\"></sup>",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup>The whole company numbered 42,360,",
			"67": "<sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup>besides their 7,337 male and female slaves; and they also had 245 male and female singers.",
			"68": "<sup class=\"versenum\">68 </sup>There were 736 horses, 245 mules,",
			"69": "<sup class=\"versenum\">69 </sup>435 camels and 6,720 donkeys.",
			"70": "<sup class=\"versenum\">70 </sup>Some of the heads of the families contributed to the work. The governor gave to the treasury 1,000 darics of gold, 50 bowls and 530 garments for priests.",
			"71": "<sup class=\"versenum\">71 </sup>Some of the heads of the families<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12492Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12492Y\"></sup> gave to the treasury for the work 20,000 darics of gold and 2,200 minas of silver.",
			"72": "<sup class=\"versenum\">72 </sup>The total given by the rest of the people was 20,000 darics of gold, 2,000 minas of silver and 67 garments for priests.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12493Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12493Z\"></sup>",
			"73": "<sup class=\"versenum\">73 </sup>The priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers, the musicians and the temple servants,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12494AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12494AA\"></sup> along with certain of the people and the rest of the Israelites, settled in their own towns.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12494AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12494AB\"></sup>When the seventh month came and the Israelites had settled in their towns,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12494AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12494AC\"></sup>"
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum mid-paragraph\">8 </span><sup class=\"versenum mid-paragraph\">1 </sup>all the people came together as one in the square before the Water Gate.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12495A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12495A\"></sup> They told Ezra the teacher of the Law to bring out the Book of the Law of Moses,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12495B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12495B\"></sup> which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded for Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So on the first day of the seventh month<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12496C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12496C\"></sup> Ezra the priest brought the Law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12496D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12496D\"></sup> before the assembly, which was made up of men and women and all who were able to understand.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He read it aloud from daybreak till noon as he faced the square before the Water Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12497E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12497E\"></sup> in the presence of the men, women and others who could understand. And all the people listened attentively to the Book of the Law.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Ezra the teacher of the Law stood on a high wooden platform<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12498F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12498F\"></sup> built for the occasion. Beside him on his right stood Mattithiah, Shema, Anaiah, Uriah, Hilkiah and Maaseiah; and on his left were Pedaiah, Mishael, Malkijah, Hashum, Hashbaddanah, Zechariah and Meshullam.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Ezra opened the book. All the people could see him because he was standing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12499G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12499G\"></sup> above them; and as he opened it, the people all stood up.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Ezra praised the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the great God; and all the people lifted their hands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12500H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12500H\"></sup> and responded, “Amen! Amen!” Then they bowed down and worshiped the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with their faces to the ground.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The Levites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12501I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12501I\"></sup>—Jeshua, Bani, Sherebiah, Jamin, Akkub, Shabbethai, Hodiah, Maaseiah, Kelita, Azariah, Jozabad, Hanan and Pelaiah—instructed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12501J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12501J\"></sup> the people in the Law while the people were standing there.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They read from the Book of the Law of God, making it clear and giving the meaning so that the people understood what was being read.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Nehemiah the governor, Ezra the priest and teacher of the Law, and the Levites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12503K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12503K\"></sup> who were instructing the people said to them all, “This day is holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God. Do not mourn or weep.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12503L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12503L\"></sup> For all the people had been weeping as they listened to the words of the Law.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Nehemiah said, “Go and enjoy choice food and sweet drinks, and send some to those who have nothing<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12504M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12504M\"></sup> prepared. This day is holy to our Lord. Do not grieve, for the joy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12504N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12504N\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is your strength.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The Levites calmed all the people, saying, “Be still, for this is a holy day. Do not grieve.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then all the people went away to eat and drink, to send portions of food and to celebrate with great joy,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12506O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12506O\"></sup> because they now understood the words that had been made known to them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>On the second day of the month, the heads of all the families, along with the priests and the Levites, gathered around Ezra the teacher to give attention to the words of the Law.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They found written in the Law, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded through Moses, that the Israelites were to live in temporary shelters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12508P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12508P\"></sup> during the festival of the seventh month",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and that they should proclaim this word and spread it throughout their towns and in Jerusalem: “Go out into the hill country and bring back branches from olive and wild olive trees, and from myrtles, palms and shade trees, to make temporary shelters”—as it is written.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So the people went out and brought back branches and built themselves temporary shelters on their own roofs, in their courtyards, in the courts of the house of God and in the square by the Water Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12510Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12510Q\"></sup> and the one by the Gate of Ephraim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12510R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12510R\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The whole company that had returned from exile built temporary shelters and lived in them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12511S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12511S\"></sup> From the days of Joshua son of Nun until that day, the Israelites had not celebrated<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12511T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12511T\"></sup> it like this. And their joy was very great.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Day after day, from the first day to the last, Ezra read<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12512U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12512U\"></sup> from the Book of the Law<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12512V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12512V\"></sup> of God. They celebrated the festival for seven days, and on the eighth day, in accordance with the regulation,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12512W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12512W\"></sup> there was an assembly.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12512X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12512X\"></sup>"
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>On the twenty-fourth day of the same month, the Israelites gathered together, fasting and wearing sackcloth and putting dust on their heads.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12513A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12513A\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Those of Israelite descent had separated themselves from all foreigners.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12514B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12514B\"></sup> They stood in their places and confessed their sins and the sins of their ancestors.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12514C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12514C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They stood where they were and read from the Book of the Law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God for a quarter of the day, and spent another quarter in confession and in worshiping the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Standing on the stairs of the Levites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12516D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12516D\"></sup> were Jeshua, Bani, Kadmiel, Shebaniah, Bunni, Sherebiah, Bani and Kenani. They cried out with loud voices to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the Levites—Jeshua, Kadmiel, Bani, Hashabneiah, Sherebiah, Hodiah, Shebaniah and Pethahiah—said: “Stand up and praise the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12517E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12517E\"></sup> who is from everlasting to everlasting.”“Blessed be your glorious name,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12517F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12517F\"></sup> and may it be exalted above all blessing and praise.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You alone are the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12518G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12518G\"></sup> You made the heavens,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12518H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12518H\"></sup> even the highest heavens, and all their starry host,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12518I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12518I\"></sup> the earth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12518J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12518J\"></sup> and all that is on it, the seas<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12518K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12518K\"></sup> and all that is in them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12518L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12518L\"></sup> You give life to everything, and the multitudes of heaven<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12518M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12518M\"></sup> worship you.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“You are the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, who chose Abram<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12519N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12519N\"></sup> and brought him out of Ur of the Chaldeans<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12519O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12519O\"></sup> and named him Abraham.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12519P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12519P\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You found his heart faithful to you, and you made a covenant with him to give to his descendants the land of the Canaanites, Hittites, Amorites, Perizzites, Jebusites and Girgashites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12520Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12520Q\"></sup> You have kept your promise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12520R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12520R\"></sup> because you are righteous.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12520S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12520S\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“You saw the suffering of our ancestors in Egypt;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12521T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12521T\"></sup> you heard their cry at the Red Sea.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12521U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12521U\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You sent signs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12522V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12522V\"></sup> and wonders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12522W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12522W\"></sup> against Pharaoh, against all his officials and all the people of his land, for you knew how arrogantly the Egyptians treated them. You made a name<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12522X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12522X\"></sup> for yourself,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12522Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12522Y\"></sup> which remains to this day.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You divided the sea before them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12523Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12523Z\"></sup> so that they passed through it on dry ground, but you hurled their pursuers into the depths,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12523AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12523AA\"></sup> like a stone into mighty waters.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12523AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12523AB\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>By day<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12524AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12524AC\"></sup> you led<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12524AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12524AD\"></sup> them with a pillar of cloud,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12524AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12524AE\"></sup> and by night with a pillar of fire to give them light on the way they were to take.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“You came down on Mount Sinai;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12525AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12525AF\"></sup> you spoke<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12525AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12525AG\"></sup> to them from heaven.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12525AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12525AH\"></sup> You gave them regulations and laws that are just<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12525AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12525AI\"></sup> and right, and decrees and commands that are good.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12525AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12525AJ\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You made known to them your holy Sabbath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12526AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12526AK\"></sup> and gave them commands, decrees and laws through your servant Moses.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>In their hunger you gave them bread from heaven<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12527AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12527AL\"></sup> and in their thirst you brought them water from the rock;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12527AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12527AM\"></sup> you told them to go in and take possession of the land you had sworn with uplifted hand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12527AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12527AN\"></sup> to give them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12527AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12527AO\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“But they, our ancestors, became arrogant and stiff-necked,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12528AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12528AP\"></sup> and they did not obey your commands.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12528AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12528AQ\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They refused to listen and failed to remember<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12529AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12529AR\"></sup> the miracles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12529AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12529AS\"></sup> you performed among them. They became stiff-necked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12529AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12529AT\"></sup> and in their rebellion appointed a leader in order to return to their slavery.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12529AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12529AU\"></sup> But you are a forgiving God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12529AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12529AV\"></sup> gracious and compassionate,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12529AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12529AW\"></sup> slow to anger<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12529AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12529AX\"></sup> and abounding in love.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12529AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12529AY\"></sup> Therefore you did not desert them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12529AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12529AZ\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>even when they cast for themselves an image of a calf<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12530BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12530BA\"></sup> and said, ‘This is your god, who brought you up out of Egypt,’ or when they committed awful blasphemies.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12530BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12530BB\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Because of your great compassion you did not abandon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12531BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12531BC\"></sup> them in the wilderness. By day the pillar of cloud<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12531BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12531BD\"></sup> did not fail to guide them on their path, nor the pillar of fire by night to shine on the way they were to take.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You gave your good Spirit<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12532BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12532BE\"></sup> to instruct<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12532BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12532BF\"></sup> them. You did not withhold your manna<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12532BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12532BG\"></sup> from their mouths, and you gave them water<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12532BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12532BH\"></sup> for their thirst.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>For forty years<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12533BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12533BI\"></sup> you sustained them in the wilderness; they lacked nothing,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12533BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12533BJ\"></sup> their clothes did not wear out nor did their feet become swollen.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12533BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12533BK\"></sup>",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“You gave them kingdoms and nations, allotting to them even the remotest frontiers. They took over the country of Sihon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12534BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12534BL\"></sup> king of Heshbon and the country of Og king of Bashan.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12534BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12534BM\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>You made their children as numerous as the stars in the sky,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12535BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12535BN\"></sup> and you brought them into the land that you told their parents to enter and possess.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Their children went in and took possession of the land.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12536BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12536BO\"></sup> You subdued<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12536BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12536BP\"></sup> before them the Canaanites, who lived in the land; you gave the Canaanites into their hands, along with their kings and the peoples of the land, to deal with them as they pleased.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>They captured fortified cities and fertile land;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12537BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12537BQ\"></sup> they took possession of houses filled with all kinds of good things,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12537BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12537BR\"></sup> wells already dug, vineyards, olive groves and fruit trees in abundance. They ate to the full and were well-nourished;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12537BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12537BS\"></sup> they reveled in your great goodness.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12537BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12537BT\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“But they were disobedient and rebelled against you; they turned their backs on your law.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12538BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12538BU\"></sup> They killed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12538BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12538BV\"></sup> your prophets,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12538BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12538BW\"></sup> who had warned them in order to turn them back to you; they committed awful blasphemies.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12538BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12538BX\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So you delivered them into the hands of their enemies,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12539BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12539BY\"></sup> who oppressed them. But when they were oppressed they cried out to you. From heaven you heard them, and in your great compassion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12539BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12539BZ\"></sup> you gave them deliverers,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12539CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12539CA\"></sup> who rescued them from the hand of their enemies.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“But as soon as they were at rest, they again did what was evil in your sight.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12540CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12540CB\"></sup> Then you abandoned them to the hand of their enemies so that they ruled over them. And when they cried out to you again, you heard from heaven, and in your compassion<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12540CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12540CC\"></sup> you delivered them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12540CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12540CD\"></sup> time after time.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“You warned<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12541CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12541CE\"></sup> them in order to turn them back to your law, but they became arrogant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12541CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12541CF\"></sup> and disobeyed your commands. They sinned against your ordinances, of which you said, ‘The person who obeys them will live by them.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12541CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12541CG\"></sup> Stubbornly they turned their backs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12541CH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CH&quot;&gt;CH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12541CH\"></sup> on you, became stiff-necked<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12541CI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CI&quot;&gt;CI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12541CI\"></sup> and refused to listen.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12541CJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CJ&quot;&gt;CJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12541CJ\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>For many years you were patient with them. By your Spirit you warned them through your prophets.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12542CK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CK&quot;&gt;CK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12542CK\"></sup> Yet they paid no attention, so you gave them into the hands of the neighboring peoples.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12542CL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CL&quot;&gt;CL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12542CL\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But in your great mercy you did not put an end<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12543CM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CM&quot;&gt;CM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12543CM\"></sup> to them or abandon them, for you are a gracious and merciful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12543CN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CN&quot;&gt;CN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12543CN\"></sup> God.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“Now therefore, our God, the great God, mighty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12544CO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CO&quot;&gt;CO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12544CO\"></sup> and awesome,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12544CP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CP&quot;&gt;CP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12544CP\"></sup> who keeps his covenant of love,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12544CQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CQ&quot;&gt;CQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12544CQ\"></sup> do not let all this hardship seem trifling in your eyes—the hardship<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12544CR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CR&quot;&gt;CR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12544CR\"></sup> that has come on us, on our kings and leaders, on our priests and prophets, on our ancestors and all your people, from the days of the kings of Assyria until today.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>In all that has happened to us, you have remained righteous;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12545CS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CS&quot;&gt;CS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12545CS\"></sup> you have acted faithfully, while we acted wickedly.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12545CT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CT&quot;&gt;CT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12545CT\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Our kings,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12546CU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CU&quot;&gt;CU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12546CU\"></sup> our leaders, our priests and our ancestors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12546CV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CV&quot;&gt;CV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12546CV\"></sup> did not follow your law; they did not pay attention to your commands or the statutes you warned them to keep.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Even while they were in their kingdom, enjoying your great goodness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12547CW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CW&quot;&gt;CW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12547CW\"></sup> to them in the spacious and fertile land you gave them, they did not serve you<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12547CX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CX&quot;&gt;CX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12547CX\"></sup> or turn from their evil ways.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“But see, we are slaves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12548CY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CY&quot;&gt;CY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12548CY\"></sup> today, slaves in the land you gave our ancestors so they could eat its fruit and the other good things it produces.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Because of our sins, its abundant harvest goes to the kings you have placed over us. They rule over our bodies and our cattle as they please. We are in great distress.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12549CZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CZ&quot;&gt;CZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12549CZ\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>“In view of all this, we are making a binding agreement,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12550DA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DA&quot;&gt;DA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12550DA\"></sup> putting it in writing,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12550DB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference DB&quot;&gt;DB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12550DB\"></sup> and our leaders, our Levites and our priests are affixing their seals to it.”"
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>Those who sealed it were:Nehemiah the governor, the son of Hakaliah.Zedekiah,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Seraiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12552A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12552A\"></sup> Azariah, Jeremiah,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Pashhur,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12553B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12553B\"></sup> Amariah, Malkijah,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Hattush, Shebaniah, Malluk,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Harim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12555C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12555C\"></sup> Meremoth, Obadiah,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Daniel, Ginnethon, Baruch,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Meshullam, Abijah, Mijamin,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Maaziah, Bilgai and Shemaiah.These were the priests.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12558D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12558D\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The Levites:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12559E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12559E\"></sup>Jeshua son of Azaniah, Binnui of the sons of Henadad, Kadmiel,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and their associates: Shebaniah,Hodiah, Kelita, Pelaiah, Hanan,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Mika, Rehob, Hashabiah,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Zakkur, Sherebiah, Shebaniah,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Hodiah, Bani and Beninu.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The leaders of the people:Parosh, Pahath-Moab, Elam, Zattu, Bani,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Bunni, Azgad, Bebai,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Adonijah, Bigvai, Adin,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12566F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12566F\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Ater, Hezekiah, Azzur,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Hodiah, Hashum, Bezai,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Hariph, Anathoth, Nebai,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Magpiash, Meshullam, Hezir,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12570G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12570G\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Meshezabel, Zadok, Jaddua,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Pelatiah, Hanan, Anaiah,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Hoshea, Hananiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12573H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12573H\"></sup> Hasshub,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Hallohesh, Pilha, Shobek,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Rehum, Hashabnah, Maaseiah,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Ahiah, Hanan, Anan,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Malluk, Harim and Baanah.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“The rest of the people—priests, Levites, gatekeepers, musicians, temple servants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12578I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12578I\"></sup> and all who separated themselves from the neighboring peoples<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12578J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12578J\"></sup> for the sake of the Law of God, together with their wives and all their sons and daughters who are able to understand—",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>all these now join their fellow Israelites the nobles, and bind themselves with a curse and an oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12579K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12579K\"></sup> to follow the Law of God given through Moses the servant of God and to obey carefully all the commands, regulations and decrees of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our Lord.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>“We promise not to give our daughters in marriage to the peoples around us or take their daughters for our sons.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12580L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12580L\"></sup>",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“When the neighboring peoples bring merchandise or grain to sell on the Sabbath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12581M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12581M\"></sup> we will not buy from them on the Sabbath or on any holy day. Every seventh year we will forgo working the land<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12581N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12581N\"></sup> and will cancel all debts.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12581O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12581O\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“We assume the responsibility for carrying out the commands to give a third of a shekel each year for the service of the house of our God:",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>for the bread set out on the table;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12583P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12583P\"></sup> for the regular grain offerings and burnt offerings; for the offerings on the Sabbaths, at the New Moon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12583Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12583Q\"></sup> feasts and at the appointed festivals; for the holy offerings; for sin offerings to make atonement for Israel; and for all the duties of the house of our God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12583R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12583R\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“We—the priests, the Levites and the people—have cast lots<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12584S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12584S\"></sup> to determine when each of our families is to bring to the house of our God at set times each year a contribution of wood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12584T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12584T\"></sup> to burn on the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, as it is written in the Law.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>“We also assume responsibility for bringing to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> each year the firstfruits<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12585U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12585U\"></sup> of our crops and of every fruit tree.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12585V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12585V\"></sup>",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“As it is also written in the Law, we will bring the firstborn<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12586W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12586W\"></sup> of our sons and of our cattle, of our herds and of our flocks to the house of our God, to the priests ministering there.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12586X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12586X\"></sup>",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>“Moreover, we will bring to the storerooms of the house of our God, to the priests, the first of our ground meal, of our grain offerings, of the fruit of all our trees and of our new wine and olive oil.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12587Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12587Y\"></sup> And we will bring a tithe<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12587Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12587Z\"></sup> of our crops to the Levites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12587AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12587AA\"></sup> for it is the Levites who collect the tithes in all the towns where we work.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12587AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12587AB\"></sup>",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>A priest descended from Aaron is to accompany the Levites when they receive the tithes, and the Levites are to bring a tenth of the tithes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12588AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12588AC\"></sup> up to the house of our God, to the storerooms of the treasury.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>The people of Israel, including the Levites, are to bring their contributions of grain, new wine and olive oil to the storerooms, where the articles for the sanctuary and for the ministering priests, the gatekeepers and the musicians are also kept.“We will not neglect the house of our God.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12589AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12589AD\"></sup>"
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>Now the leaders of the people settled in Jerusalem. The rest of the people cast lots to bring one out of every ten of them to live in Jerusalem,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12590B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12590B\"></sup> the holy city,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12590C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12590C\"></sup> while the remaining nine were to stay in their own towns.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12590D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12590D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The people commended all who volunteered to live in Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>These are the provincial leaders who settled in Jerusalem (now some Israelites, priests, Levites, temple servants and descendants of Solomon’s servants lived in the towns of Judah, each on their own property in the various towns,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12592E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12592E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>while other people from both Judah and Benjamin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12593F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12593F\"></sup> lived in Jerusalem):<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12593G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12593G\"></sup>From the descendants of Judah:Athaiah son of Uzziah, the son of Zechariah, the son of Amariah, the son of Shephatiah, the son of Mahalalel, a descendant of Perez;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and Maaseiah son of Baruch, the son of Kol-Hozeh, the son of Hazaiah, the son of Adaiah, the son of Joiarib, the son of Zechariah, a descendant of Shelah.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The descendants of Perez who lived in Jerusalem totaled 468 men of standing.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>From the descendants of Benjamin:Sallu son of Meshullam, the son of Joed, the son of Pedaiah, the son of Kolaiah, the son of Maaseiah, the son of Ithiel, the son of Jeshaiah,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and his followers, Gabbai and Sallai—928 men.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Joel son of Zikri was their chief officer, and Judah son of Hassenuah was over the New Quarter of the city.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>From the priests:Jedaiah; the son of Joiarib; Jakin;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Seraiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12600H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12600H\"></sup> son of Hilkiah, the son of Meshullam, the son of Zadok, the son of Meraioth, the son of Ahitub,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12600I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12600I\"></sup> the official in charge of the house of God,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and their associates, who carried on work for the temple—822 men; Adaiah son of Jeroham, the son of Pelaliah, the son of Amzi, the son of Zechariah, the son of Pashhur, the son of Malkijah,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and his associates, who were heads of families—242 men; Amashsai son of Azarel, the son of Ahzai, the son of Meshillemoth, the son of Immer,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and his associates, who were men of standing—128. Their chief officer was Zabdiel son of Haggedolim.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>From the Levites:Shemaiah son of Hasshub, the son of Azrikam, the son of Hashabiah, the son of Bunni;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Shabbethai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12605J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12605J\"></sup> and Jozabad,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12605K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12605K\"></sup> two of the heads of the Levites, who had charge of the outside work of the house of God;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Mattaniah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12606L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12606L\"></sup> son of Mika, the son of Zabdi, the son of Asaph,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12606M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12606M\"></sup> the director who led in thanksgiving and prayer; Bakbukiah, second among his associates; and Abda son of Shammua, the son of Galal, the son of Jeduthun.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12606N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12606N\"></sup>",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The Levites in the holy city<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12607O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12607O\"></sup> totaled 284.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The gatekeepers:Akkub, Talmon and their associates, who kept watch at the gates—172 men.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The rest of the Israelites, with the priests and Levites, were in all the towns of Judah, each on their ancestral property.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The temple servants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12610P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12610P\"></sup> lived on the hill of Ophel, and Ziha and Gishpa were in charge of them.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The chief officer of the Levites in Jerusalem was Uzzi son of Bani, the son of Hashabiah, the son of Mattaniah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12611Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12611Q\"></sup> the son of Mika. Uzzi was one of Asaph’s descendants, who were the musicians responsible for the service of the house of God.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The musicians<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12612R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12612R\"></sup> were under the king’s orders, which regulated their daily activity.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Pethahiah son of Meshezabel, one of the descendants of Zerah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12613S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12613S\"></sup> son of Judah, was the king’s agent in all affairs relating to the people.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>As for the villages with their fields, some of the people of Judah lived in Kiriath Arba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12614T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12614T\"></sup> and its surrounding settlements, in Dibon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12614U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12614U\"></sup> and its settlements, in Jekabzeel and its villages,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>in Jeshua, in Moladah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12615V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12615V\"></sup> in Beth Pelet,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12615W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12615W\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>in Hazar Shual,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12616X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12616X\"></sup> in Beersheba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12616Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12616Y\"></sup> and its settlements,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>in Ziklag,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12617Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12617Z\"></sup> in Mekonah and its settlements,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>in En Rimmon, in Zorah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12618AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12618AA\"></sup> in Jarmuth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12618AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12618AB\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Zanoah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12619AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12619AC\"></sup> Adullam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12619AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12619AD\"></sup> and their villages, in Lachish<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12619AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12619AE\"></sup> and its fields, and in Azekah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12619AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12619AF\"></sup> and its settlements. So they were living all the way from Beersheba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12619AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12619AG\"></sup> to the Valley of Hinnom.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The descendants of the Benjamites from Geba<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12620AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12620AH\"></sup> lived in Mikmash,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12620AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12620AI\"></sup> Aija, Bethel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12620AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12620AJ\"></sup> and its settlements,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>in Anathoth,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12621AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12621AK\"></sup> Nob<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12621AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12621AL\"></sup> and Ananiah,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>in Hazor,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12622AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12622AM\"></sup> Ramah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12622AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12622AN\"></sup> and Gittaim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12622AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12622AO\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>in Hadid, Zeboim<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12623AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12623AP\"></sup> and Neballat,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>in Lod and Ono,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12624AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12624AQ\"></sup> and in Ge Harashim.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Some of the divisions of the Levites of Judah settled in Benjamin."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>These were the priests<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12626A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12626A\"></sup> and Levites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12626B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12626B\"></sup> who returned with Zerubbabel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12626C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12626C\"></sup> son of Shealtiel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12626D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12626D\"></sup> and with Joshua:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12626E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12626E\"></sup>Seraiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12626F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12626F\"></sup> Jeremiah, Ezra,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Amariah, Malluk, Hattush,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Shekaniah, Rehum, Meremoth,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Iddo,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12629G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12629G\"></sup> Ginnethon, Abijah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12629H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12629H\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Mijamin, Moadiah, Bilgah,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Shemaiah, Joiarib, Jedaiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12631I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12631I\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Sallu, Amok, Hilkiah and Jedaiah.These were the leaders of the priests and their associates in the days of Joshua.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The Levites were Jeshua,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12633J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12633J\"></sup> Binnui, Kadmiel, Sherebiah, Judah, and also Mattaniah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12633K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12633K\"></sup> who, together with his associates, was in charge of the songs of thanksgiving.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Bakbukiah and Unni, their associates, stood opposite them in the services.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Joshua was the father of Joiakim, Joiakim the father of Eliashib,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12635L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12635L\"></sup> Eliashib the father of Joiada,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Joiada the father of Jonathan, and Jonathan the father of Jaddua.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>In the days of Joiakim, these were the heads of the priestly families:of Seraiah’s family, Meraiah;of Jeremiah’s, Hananiah;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>of Ezra’s, Meshullam;of Amariah’s, Jehohanan;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>of Malluk’s, Jonathan;of Shekaniah’s, Joseph;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>of Harim’s, Adna;of Meremoth’s, Helkai;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>of Iddo’s,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12641M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12641M\"></sup> Zechariah;of Ginnethon’s, Meshullam;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>of Abijah’s,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12642N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12642N\"></sup> Zikri;of Miniamin’s and of Moadiah’s, Piltai;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>of Bilgah’s, Shammua;of Shemaiah’s, Jehonathan;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>of Joiarib’s, Mattenai;of Jedaiah’s, Uzzi;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>of Sallu’s, Kallai;of Amok’s, Eber;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>of Hilkiah’s, Hashabiah;of Jedaiah’s, Nethanel.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The family heads of the Levites in the days of Eliashib, Joiada, Johanan and Jaddua, as well as those of the priests, were recorded in the reign of Darius the Persian.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The family heads among the descendants of Levi up to the time of Johanan son of Eliashib were recorded in the book of the annals.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And the leaders of the Levites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12649O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12649O\"></sup> were Hashabiah, Sherebiah, Jeshua son of Kadmiel, and their associates, who stood opposite them to give praise and thanksgiving, one section responding to the other, as prescribed by David the man of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12649P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12649P\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Mattaniah, Bakbukiah, Obadiah, Meshullam, Talmon and Akkub were gatekeepers who guarded the storerooms at the gates.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>They served in the days of Joiakim son of Joshua, the son of Jozadak, and in the days of Nehemiah the governor and of Ezra the priest, the teacher of the Law.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>At the dedication<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12652Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12652Q\"></sup> of the wall of Jerusalem, the Levites were sought out from where they lived and were brought to Jerusalem to celebrate joyfully the dedication with songs of thanksgiving and with the music of cymbals,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12652R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12652R\"></sup> harps and lyres.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12652S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12652S\"></sup>",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The musicians also were brought together from the region around Jerusalem—from the villages of the Netophathites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12653T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12653T\"></sup>",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>from Beth Gilgal, and from the area of Geba and Azmaveth, for the musicians had built villages for themselves around Jerusalem.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>When the priests and Levites had purified themselves ceremonially, they purified the people,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12655U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12655U\"></sup> the gates and the wall.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>I had the leaders of Judah go up on top of the wall. I also assigned two large choirs to give thanks. One was to proceed on top of the wall to the right, toward the Dung Gate.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12656V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12656V\"></sup>",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Hoshaiah and half the leaders of Judah followed them,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>along with Azariah, Ezra, Meshullam,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Judah, Benjamin,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12659W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12659W\"></sup> Shemaiah, Jeremiah,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>as well as some priests with trumpets,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12660X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12660X\"></sup> and also Zechariah son of Jonathan, the son of Shemaiah, the son of Mattaniah, the son of Micaiah, the son of Zakkur, the son of Asaph,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>and his associates—Shemaiah, Azarel, Milalai, Gilalai, Maai, Nethanel, Judah and Hanani—with musical instruments<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12661Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12661Y\"></sup> prescribed by David the man of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12661Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12661Z\"></sup> Ezra<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12661AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12661AA\"></sup> the teacher of the Law led the procession.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>At the Fountain Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12662AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12662AB\"></sup> they continued directly up the steps of the City of David on the ascent to the wall and passed above the site of David’s palace to the Water Gate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12662AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12662AC\"></sup> on the east.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>The second choir proceeded in the opposite direction. I followed them on top of the wall, together with half the people—past the Tower of the Ovens<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12663AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12663AD\"></sup> to the Broad Wall,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12663AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12663AE\"></sup>",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>over the Gate of Ephraim,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12664AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12664AF\"></sup> the Jeshanah Gate,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12664AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12664AG\"></sup> the Fish Gate,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12664AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12664AH\"></sup> the Tower of Hananel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12664AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12664AI\"></sup> and the Tower of the Hundred,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12664AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12664AJ\"></sup> as far as the Sheep Gate.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12664AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12664AK\"></sup> At the Gate of the Guard they stopped.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>The two choirs that gave thanks then took their places in the house of God; so did I, together with half the officials,",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>as well as the priests—Eliakim, Maaseiah, Miniamin, Micaiah, Elioenai, Zechariah and Hananiah with their trumpets—",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>and also Maaseiah, Shemaiah, Eleazar, Uzzi, Jehohanan, Malkijah, Elam and Ezer. The choirs sang under the direction of Jezrahiah.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And on that day they offered great sacrifices, rejoicing because God had given them great joy. The women and children also rejoiced. The sound of rejoicing in Jerusalem could be heard far away.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>At that time men were appointed to be in charge of the storerooms<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12669AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12669AL\"></sup> for the contributions, firstfruits and tithes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12669AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12669AM\"></sup> From the fields around the towns they were to bring into the storerooms the portions required by the Law for the priests and the Levites, for Judah was pleased with the ministering priests and Levites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12669AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12669AN\"></sup>",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>They performed the service of their God and the service of purification, as did also the musicians and gatekeepers, according to the commands of David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12670AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12670AO\"></sup> and his son Solomon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12670AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12670AP\"></sup>",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>For long ago, in the days of David and Asaph,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12671AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12671AQ\"></sup> there had been directors for the musicians and for the songs of praise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12671AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12671AR\"></sup> and thanksgiving to God.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>So in the days of Zerubbabel and of Nehemiah, all Israel contributed the daily portions for the musicians and the gatekeepers. They also set aside the portion for the other Levites, and the Levites set aside the portion for the descendants of Aaron.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12672AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12672AS\"></sup>"
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>On that day the Book of Moses was read aloud in the hearing of the people and there it was found written that no Ammonite or Moabite should ever be admitted into the assembly of God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12673A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12673A\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>because they had not met the Israelites with food and water but had hired Balaam<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12674B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12674B\"></sup> to call a curse down on them.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12674C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12674C\"></sup> (Our God, however, turned the curse into a blessing.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12674D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12674D\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When the people heard this law, they excluded from Israel all who were of foreign descent.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12675E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12675E\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Before this, Eliashib the priest had been put in charge of the storerooms<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12676F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12676F\"></sup> of the house of our God. He was closely associated with Tobiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12676G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12676G\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and he had provided him with a large room formerly used to store the grain offerings and incense and temple articles, and also the tithes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12677H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12677H\"></sup> of grain, new wine and olive oil prescribed for the Levites, musicians and gatekeepers, as well as the contributions for the priests.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But while all this was going on, I was not in Jerusalem, for in the thirty-second year of Artaxerxes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12678I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12678I\"></sup> king of Babylon I had returned to the king. Some time later I asked his permission",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and came back to Jerusalem. Here I learned about the evil thing Eliashib<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12679J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12679J\"></sup> had done in providing Tobiah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12679K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12679K\"></sup> a room in the courts of the house of God.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I was greatly displeased and threw all Tobiah’s household goods out of the room.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12680L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12680L\"></sup>",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>I gave orders to purify the rooms,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12681M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12681M\"></sup> and then I put back into them the equipment of the house of God, with the grain offerings and the incense.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12681N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12681N\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>I also learned that the portions assigned to the Levites had not been given to them,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12682O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12682O\"></sup> and that all the Levites and musicians responsible for the service had gone back to their own fields.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12682P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12682P\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So I rebuked the officials and asked them, “Why is the house of God neglected?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12683Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12683Q\"></sup> Then I called them together and stationed them at their posts.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>All Judah brought the tithes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12684R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12684R\"></sup> of grain, new wine and olive oil into the storerooms.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12684S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12684S\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I put Shelemiah the priest, Zadok the scribe, and a Levite named Pedaiah in charge of the storerooms and made Hanan son of Zakkur, the son of Mattaniah, their assistant, because they were considered trustworthy. They were made responsible for distributing the supplies to their fellow Levites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12685T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12685T\"></sup>",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Remember<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12686U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12686U\"></sup> me for this, my God, and do not blot out what I have so faithfully done for the house of my God and its services.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>In those days I saw people in Judah treading winepresses on the Sabbath and bringing in grain and loading it on donkeys, together with wine, grapes, figs and all other kinds of loads. And they were bringing all this into Jerusalem on the Sabbath.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12687V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12687V\"></sup> Therefore I warned them against selling food on that day.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>People from Tyre who lived in Jerusalem were bringing in fish and all kinds of merchandise and selling them in Jerusalem on the Sabbath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12688W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12688W\"></sup> to the people of Judah.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>I rebuked the nobles of Judah and said to them, “What is this wicked thing you are doing—desecrating the Sabbath day?",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Didn’t your ancestors do the same things, so that our God brought all this calamity on us and on this city?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12690X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12690X\"></sup> Now you are stirring up more wrath against Israel by desecrating the Sabbath.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12690Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12690Y\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When evening shadows fell on the gates of Jerusalem before the Sabbath,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12691Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12691Z\"></sup> I ordered the doors to be shut and not opened until the Sabbath was over. I stationed some of my own men at the gates so that no load could be brought in on the Sabbath day.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Once or twice the merchants and sellers of all kinds of goods spent the night outside Jerusalem.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But I warned them and said, “Why do you spend the night by the wall? If you do this again, I will arrest you.” From that time on they no longer came on the Sabbath.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then I commanded the Levites to purify themselves and go and guard the gates in order to keep the Sabbath day holy.Remember<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12694AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12694AA\"></sup> me for this also, my God, and show mercy to me according to your great love.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Moreover, in those days I saw men of Judah who had married<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12695AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12695AB\"></sup> women from Ashdod, Ammon and Moab.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12695AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12695AC\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Half of their children spoke the language of Ashdod or the language of one of the other peoples, and did not know how to speak the language<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12696AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12696AD\"></sup> of Judah.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>I rebuked them and called curses down on them. I beat some of the men and pulled out their hair. I made them take an oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12697AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12697AE\"></sup> in God’s name and said: “You are not to give your daughters in marriage to their sons, nor are you to take their daughters in marriage for your sons or for yourselves.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12697AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12697AF\"></sup>",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Was it not because of marriages like these that Solomon king of Israel sinned? Among the many nations there was no king like him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12698AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12698AG\"></sup> He was loved by his God,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12698AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12698AH\"></sup> and God made him king over all Israel, but even he was led into sin by foreign women.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12698AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12698AI\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Must we hear now that you too are doing all this terrible wickedness and are being unfaithful to our God by marrying<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12699AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12699AJ\"></sup> foreign women?”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>One of the sons of Joiada son of Eliashib<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12700AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12700AK\"></sup> the high priest was son-in-law to Sanballat<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12700AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12700AL\"></sup> the Horonite. And I drove him away from me.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Remember<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12701AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12701AM\"></sup> them, my God, because they defiled the priestly office and the covenant of the priesthood and of the Levites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12701AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12701AN\"></sup>",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So I purified the priests and the Levites of everything foreign,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12702AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12702AO\"></sup> and assigned them duties, each to his own task.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>I also made provision for contributions of wood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12703AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12703AP\"></sup> at designated times, and for the firstfruits.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12703AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12703AQ\"></sup>Remember<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12703AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12703AR\"></sup> me with favor, my God."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;